        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-13T15:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-13T15:30:00-05:00" n="54"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d54">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">United States Delegation Journal</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-chapter-heading" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1946-08-13T21:30:00+01:00">August 13, 1946, 9:30 p.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> (PC) (Journal) 15</p>
                <p>Mr. <persName>Dunn</persName> (U.S.) said that his delegation considered it
                    inadvisable for a representative of any state which prepared the draft peace
                    treaties to be chosen as <hi rend="italic">rapporteur</hi> of any of the
                    commissions. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_VAY1">Vyshinsky</persName> (U.S.S.R.)
                    disagreed with Mr. <persName>Dunn</persName>’s view. Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_EL1">Egeland</persName> (South Africa) was nominated for
                    Chairman of the Commission by M. <persName corresp="#p_VAY1"
                        >Vyshinsky</persName> and seconded by Dr. <persName corresp="#p_EHV1"
                        >Evatt</persName> (Australia). He was unanimously elected. Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MSR1">McNeil</persName> (U.K.) proposed M. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MDZ1">Manouilsky</persName> (Ukraine) as Vice Chairman and he
                    was unanimously elected by acclamation. The election of a <hi rend="italic"
                        >rapporteur</hi> was postponed until the next meeting.</p>
            </div>
